            <ul class="product-accordion" id="careers-accordion">
                <li>
                    <div class="product-line-title clear">
                        <h4 class="mid-grey-upper inline-block">Management/Professional <span class="mid-red-upper">Territory Manager</span> </h4>
                        <div class="red inline-block float-right clear"><div class="fa-plus-circle"></div><div class="fa-minus-circle"></div></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="hidden-product-content">
                        <p><span>Fecon is looking for a quality-driven team member to manage equipment sales. This individual is responsible for selling Fecon land clearing equipment and construction attachments to land clearing contractors and construction equipment dealers. This position is home-based with regular travel. This is a hands-on job, working with the equipment and demoing for customers and also training operators. The Territory Manager will occasionally partner with the engineering and production departments to consider revisions and updates.</span></p>
<p><span> </span></p>
<p><span>Our Territory Managers are responsible for building relationships – both setting up new relationships and nurturing existing relationships with our dealers and customers. Additionally, responsibilities include developing sales targets among land clearing contractors.</span></p>
<p><span> </span></p>
<p><em><span>**Product testing and operation training is a crucial responsibility of this position.**</span></em></p>
<p><span> </span></p>
<p><span>Skills and Knowledge:</span></p>
<ul>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Knowledge of heavy equipment/construction equipment is <strong>required</strong>.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Two years of experience in sales of construction equipment is helpful.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Computer literate.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Strong work ethic.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Extremely organized with excellent written and oral communication skills.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Must be able to handle cold calls.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Physical ability to safely climb onto and around the equipment.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Experience and physical ability to safely drive and operate machinery.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Must have valid drivers license.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span>Benefits: click here to view company benefits.</span></p>
<p><span>Please submit resume and salary history in your email or fax. </span></p>
<p><span> </span></p>
                        <div class="button-sm upper clear float-left">
                            <a href="mailto:hr@fecon.com"> apply now by email<span class="fa-caret-right"></span></a>
</div>
                        <p class="small-grey-subtitle apply-fax">
                            Apply by fax: 513-696-4431
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <div class="product-line-title clear">
                        <h4 class="mid-grey-upper inline-block">Management/Professional <span class="mid-red-upper">Mechanical Design Engineer</span> </h4>
                        <div class="red inline-block float-right clear"><div class="fa-plus-circle"></div><div class="fa-minus-circle"></div></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="hidden-product-content">
                        <p><span>The mechanical engineer will be responsible for new product development activities and assisting the lead project engineer in day to day project activities. The activities will include responsibilities of mechanical system design of Fecon products, as well as the implementation of designs. This position includes (but is not limited to) the following responsibilities along with the primary responsibility of subsystem design as well as complete product design utilizing 3D design software. Five plus years experience preferred.</span></p>
<ul>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Uses computer-assisted engineering software to design, develop, and/or modify products, applying engineering principles.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Prepares product or system layouts, detailed manufacturing drawings and schematics.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Determines feasibility of designs considering costs, time limitations, planning, and other technical and economic factors.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Analyzes engineering proposals, process requirements, and related technical data pertaining to design.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Analyzes product or equipment specifications and performance requirements to determine designs that can be produced by existing manufacturing or processing facilities and methods.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Confers with research and other engineering personnel and prepares design modifications as required.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Evaluates engineering test results for possible application to development of systems or other uses.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span> </span></p>
<p><span>Engineering and Technology</span></p>
<ul>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>BS in mechanical engineering required.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Three to five years experience preferred.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Knowledge of the practical application of engineering science and technology. This includes applying principles, techniques, procedures, and equipment to the design and production of various Products.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span> </span></p>
<p><span>Skills Required</span></p>
<ul>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Strong ability to multi-task.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Knowledge of BOM’s.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Good oral and written communication skills.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Software skills: Solid Works or Solid Edge; AutoCAD is a plus.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Experience with Microsoft Excel and Microsoft Word.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Physical ability to safely climb onto and around the equipment.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span>Knowledge and physical ability to safely drive and operate the machinery.</span></p>
<p><span> </span></p>
<p><span>Please submit resume and salary history by Email or fax. </span></p>
<p><span> </span></p>
                        <div class="button-sm upper clear float-left">
                            <a href="mailto:hr@fecon.com"> apply now by email<span class="fa-caret-right"></span></a>
</div>
                        <p class="small-grey-subtitle apply-fax">
                            Apply by fax: 513-696-4431
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <div class="product-line-title clear">
                        <h4 class="mid-grey-upper inline-block">Management/Professional <span class="mid-red-upper">Shop Service Technician</span> </h4>
                        <div class="red inline-block float-right clear"><div class="fa-plus-circle"></div><div class="fa-minus-circle"></div></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="hidden-product-content">
                        <p><span>The Shop Service Technician serves conducts repairs and updates on Fecon equipment. Visiting customer sites to make repairs, address service problems to determine service and parts needs, and working with parts, service and engineering to fulfill the customer’s requirements is the bulk and main area of responsibility.</span></p>
<p><span>The Shop Service Technician is responsible for troubleshooting and repairing equipment in house and in the field. Extensive mechanical and hydraulic ability in the mobile equipment industries is required. This can include skid steers, excavators, forestry equipment, fork trucks, semi-trucks, and more. If you are someone that likes to get their hands dirty working on machines, we would like to hear from you. Automotive experience is generally not enough.</span></p>
<p><span> </span></p>
<p><span>Requirements:</span></p>
<ul>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Resourcefulness to find needed services and parts in remote locations.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Mechanical aptitude and the ability to MIG or flux core weld.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Excellent people skills working with a diverse set of customers and dealers is a must.</span></li>
<li><span><span>    </span></span><span>Commercial Driver’s License (CDL) is required.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span> </span></p>
<p><span>This job description is a general overview of qualification and duties. But circumstance may change qualification and duties of the position.</span></p>
<p><span> </span></p>
<p><span>Please submit resume and salary history by Email or fax. </span></p>
<p><span> </span></p>
