                <li>
                    <div class="product-line-title clear">
                        <h4 class="mid-grey-upper inline-block">MANAGEMENT/PROFESSIONAL <span class="mid-red-upper">PRODUCT MANAGER</span> </h4>
                        <div class="red inline-block float-right clear"><div class="fa-plus-circle"></div><div class="fa-minus-circle"></div></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="hidden-product-content">
                        <p><span>The Product Manager is an expert for the assigned products and is responsible for managing the product life cycle in processes, developing sales and marketing collateral, and ensuring all product related information is communicated to the appropriate channels.</span></p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Key performance objectives in order of priority include:  </strong></p>
<p>- Manages product position in the product life cycle in order to meet strategic objectives as well as revenue and margin goals.</p>
<p>- Creates and oversees the execution of the plan that sets the vision and objectives for category products to drive product awareness and sales.</p>
<p>- Acts as a resource to equip and enable the sales team in order to meet sales objectives.</p>
<p>- Monitors and reports on category performance to ensure alignment with company priorities.</p>
<p>- Develops business growth opportunities, evaluate feasibility for strategic fit, and lead implementation to meet company growth objectives.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Interpersonal Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ol>
<li><span>Serves as the primary product expert to assist sales team, marketing team, customers and distributors with product, technical and/or application questions; generates enthusiasm among sales team, and trains and coaches sales and marketing teams on becoming product experts. Trains Service staff on product value and specifications. </span></li>
<li><span>Collaborates with and supports the Chief Product Manager by providing updates, reports, product specification changes, product and staff performance plans and issues, market and sales activities, and gap analysis routinely or as needed.</span></li>
<li><span>Manages the prospecting and sales processes to turn sales leads into opportunities; makes presentations and conducts demonstrations internally and externally. Makes sales calls and closes deals as needed.</span></li>
<li><span>Fosters and promotes professional, ethical and positive interactions with current and potential customers, vendors and the community, through application of meticulous standards and attention to detail, personal contact, and the maintenance of strong relationships with customers, vendors, employees, manufacturing, distributors, management, and the community.</span></li>
<li><span>Encourages and seeks opportunities for collaborative efforts, seeks understanding of issues, anticipates and troubleshoots problems, and resolves urgent and ongoing matters.</span></li>
<li><span>Participates in industry associations, attends seminars, and collaborates with industry influencers to enhance and share knowledge, remain abreast of best practices, trends, and newest techniques/products, and receive/provide advice. Attends national and regional conferences, meetings, and trade shows to encourage development and to enhance quality and image of Fecon.</span></li>
<li><span>Serves as intermediary between manufacturing and vendors to report and resolve issues, gain understanding, and ensure proper application of vendor supplies. </span></li>
</ol>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Operational Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Coordinates, manages and executes strategies in all aspects of product life cycle management including product creation &amp; development, information, and data pertaining to go-to-market processes. Establishes key performance measures associated with the product and with sales.</li>
<li>Prioritizes, segments, and processes information to internal and external stakeholders to effectively communicate product information to the customers; ensures all product related information is accessible and communicated to appropriate parties in a timely manner.</li>
<li>Collaborates with production management to ensure product availability and deliverability. Provides insight from the sales perspective on manufacturing issues and works with appropriate departments to ensure resolution of product or scheduling problems.</li>
<li>Conducts competitive analysis and assists in developing strategies to drive product success including market position, product quality and pricing as well as cost reductions.</li>
<li>Conducts market and voice-of-the-customer research to determine target markets and recommend new markets, address customer needs and set pricing strategies. Shares insights and analyses with internal teams.</li>
<li>Provides feedback to management concerning product value, sustainability, and profitability and makes recommendations to introduce new products, make changes to existing items, or withdraw products from the market. Understands the impact of product withdrawal on customers currently utilizing such equipment and provides solutions to address the effect.</li>
<li>Develops and maintains a product database that includes product specifications, artwork and marketing collateral.</li>
<li>Collaborates with Engineering to create new products, develop new and/or existing product specifications and pricing; drives the collaboration with internal teams toward successful product launches.</li>
<li>Coordinates and participates in the activities associated with providing appropriate presence and coverage at trade shows and with selecting the associated materials and advertising.</li>
<li>Assists in developing, designing and implementing marketing and training collateral as well as product related presentations for assigned products.</li>
<li>Monitors vendor performance and ability to meet contracted specifications, resolving issues or determining means to sever the relationship.</li>
<li>Monitors customer service reports, identifies issues or trends, and coordinates activities to address customer concerns or needs in order to ensure customer satisfaction.</li>
</ol>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Organizational Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Collaborates with webmaster to ensure that product information presented on the website is current, accurate, and reflective of the Fecon standards and branding.</li>
<li>Generates enthusiasm and interest in new products by preparing presentations and conducting new product Gate meetings and launches.</li>
<li>Assists in the development of new marketing tools and resources, including the development of videos, photographs, brochures, press releases, or other materials.</li>
</ol>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>REQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS: </strong></p>
<p><strong>Experience:  </strong>0-1 years Sales &amp; Marketing experience. Sales Engineer experience and Mechanical aptitude are a plus. New graduates welcome. Be able to interact with various clients/prospect. Be versatile and able to adapt when in front of different clients, Overnight travel will be required (20% initially, may become 30-35%).</p>
<p><strong>Education:</strong>  Bachelor’s degree in marketing or business.</p>
