                        <p><span>The Product Specialist is an expert for their assigned products and responsible for supporting the product management of assigned products<span>, assisting in developing sales and marketing collateral, ensuring all product related information is communicated to the appropriate channels, and contributing to achieving targets for the category</span>. </span></p>
<p><strong>Key performance objectives in order of priority include: </strong> </p>
<p> - <span>Promotes and inspires opportunities for assigned product sales, market share, and profitability.</span></p>
<p> - <span>Serves as a Sales resource, directly or in support of others, to assist in meeting sales objectives of the organization.</span></p>
<p> - <span>Develops concepts and coordinates production of sales and marketing collateral to support sales and promotion of the products</span></p>
<p><span> - <span>Gathers information and assist product management to validate product opportunities and execute product decisions.</span></span></p>
<p><span> - </span>Serves as a project resource to drive go-to-market processes for new products and meet organizational goals.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Interpersonal Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ol>
<li><strong> </strong>Assists in the prospecting and the sales process to turn sales leads into opportunities; makes presentations, internally and externally, as necessary.</li>
<li> Acts as the product expert to assist all departments, customers and distributors with product, technical and/or application questions; ensures mutually  beneficial relationships are established.</li>
</ol>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Operational Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Assists in coordinating, managing and executing product and product category strategies to drive product awareness and sales.</li>
<li><span>Prioritizes, segments, and processes information to internal and external stakeholders to effectively communicate product information to the customers; ensures all product related information is accessible and<span> communicated to appropriate parties in a timely manner.</span></span></li>
<li>Conducts competitive analysis and assists in developing strategies to drive product success including market position, product quality and pricing as well as cost reductions.</li>
<li>Conducts market and voice of the customer research to determine target markets, industries associations and determine new markets, customer needs and pricing strategies.  Shares insights and analysis with internal teams.</li>
<li><span>Assists in creating existing and/or new product specifications and pricing; collaborates with internal teams to determine appropriate pricing.</span></li>
<li>Assists in identifying, coordinating and participating in tradeshows</li>
<li>Assists in developing, designing and implementing marketing and training collateral as well as product related presentations for assigned products.</li>
<li>Develops and maintains a product database that includes product specifications, artwork and marketing collateral. <span><br /></span></li>
</ol>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Organizational Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Participates in new product Gate meetings and launches.</li>
<li>Assists Product Manager in gathering appropriated data to accurately forecast product sales.</li>
<li>Assists Product Manager in meeting corporate objectives for the assigned product categories, including sales, profit, and market share.</li>
</ol>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Organizational Responsibilities</strong><strong> </strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Participates in new product Gate meetings and launches.</li>
<li>Assists Product Manager in gathering appropriated data to accurately forecast product sales.</li>
<li>Assists Product Manager in meeting corporate objectives for the assigned product categories, including sales, profit, and market share.</li>
