<p><span>This position does not manage employees.</span></p>
<p><span>Conduct field repairs, installations and updates on heavy equipment. Visit customer sites to make repairs and address service problems to determine service and parts needs. Work with Parts, Service and Engineering departments to fulfill customer requirements is a large part of the responsibilities. Train customers and dealers on the proper care and maintenance of equipment are also part of the duties. Additional responsibilities include trouble shooting, conducting product orientation and training sessions in-house and on the road. <strong>Extensive mechanical, electrical and hydraulic ability in the Heavy Equipment industry is REQUIRED.</strong> This can include skid steers, excavators, forestry equipment, fork trucks, semi-trucks and more. AUTOMOTIVE EXPERIENCE DOES NOT MEET THIS REQUIREMENT.</span></p>
